
---


@startuml

package "Alpha Insurance System" {
    "Customer" as Customer
    "Broker" as Broker
    "InsurancePolicy" as InsurancePolicy
    "Contract" as Contract
    "Claim" as Claim
    "ClaimCase" as ClaimCase
    "Estimator" as Estimator
    "Offer" as Offer
    "Payment" as Payment
    "Document" as Document
}

Customer --|> Broker : assignedTo
Broker --|> InsurancePolicy : handles
InsurancePolicy --|> Contract : associatedWith
Customer --|> Contract : has
Contract --|> Offer : generates
Offer --|> Claim : can lead to
Claim --|> ClaimCase : relatedTo
ClaimCase --|> Estimator : assessedBy
Estimator --|> ClaimCase : evaluates
ClaimCase --|> Document : includes
Document --|> Payment : usedFor
Payment --|> ClaimCase : relatedTo

note right of Customer
  - customerID
  - name
  - contactInfo
  - status
end note

note right of Broker
  - brokerID
  - name
  - contactInfo
  - department
end note

note right of InsurancePolicy
  - policyID
  - type
  - description
  - coverageDetails
end note

note right of Contract
  - contractID
  - startDate
  - endDate
  - paymentFrequency (monthly/yearly)
  - status (active, expired, canceled)
end note

note right of Offer
  - offerID
  - date
  - terms
  - approvalStatus
end note

note right of Claim
  - claimID
  - dateSubmitted
  - status (pending, under review, approved, rejected)
  - compensationAmount
end note

note right of ClaimCase
  - caseID
  - description
  - assessmentDate
  - compensationDecision
end note

note right of Estimator
  - estimatorID
  - name
  - expertiseArea
  - contactInfo
end note

note right of Document
  - documentID
  - fileName
  - uploadDate
  - type (receipt, medical report, etc.)
end note

note right of Payment
  - paymentID
  - amount
  - date
  - method (bank transfer, direct deposit, etc.)
  - status (completed, pending, failed)
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Relationships:

- **Customer** is assigned to a **Broker**.
- A **Broker** manages one or more **InsurancePolicies**.
- An **InsurancePolicy** may be associated with a **Contract**.
- A **Customer** can have multiple **Contracts**.
- A **Contract** may generate an **Offer**.
- An **Offer** can lead to a **Claim** (if accepted).
- A **Claim** may involve one or more **ClaimCases**.
- Each **ClaimCase** is assessed by an **Estimator**.
- A **ClaimCase** may include multiple **Documents**.
- **Documents** are used for **Payments**.
- A **Payment** is linked to a **ClaimCase**.

